<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="py-20" style="background:#FFFFFF">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5">
    <div class="text-center mb-10">
      <p class="sl gp mb-3">Questions</p>
      <h2 class="font-display font-black tracking-tightest" style="font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);line-height:.93;letter-spacing:-.01em">NEW HIRE FAQ.</h2>
    </div>
    <div id="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-q"><p class="font-medium text-brand-black text-sm">When do I get my first paycheck?</p><svg class="faq-arr" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#555" stroke-width="2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg></div>
        <div class="faq-a"><p style="color:#555555;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.7;padding-top:.5rem">W2 employees are on a bi-weekly schedule — your first paycheck covers the first full pay period you work in. Typically 2–3 weeks after your start date. 1099 contractors are paid upon invoice approval (Net 7–14 days).</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-q"><p class="font-medium text-brand-black text-sm">What happens if it rains or the job site is unsafe?</p><svg class="faq-arr" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#555" stroke-width="2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg></div>
        <div class="faq-a"><p style="color:#555555;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.7;padding-top:.5rem">Your PM will communicate day-of changes as early as possible — usually by 6am if weather looks bad. Never work in unsafe conditions. If you arrive and something feels wrong, call your PM immediately. W2 employees may be assigned shop work or prep tasks on rain days.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-q"><p class="font-medium text-brand-black text-sm">Who do I call if I'm running late or have an emergency?</p><svg class="faq-arr" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#555" stroke-width="2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg></div>
        <div class="faq-a"><p style="color:#555555;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.7;padding-top:.5rem">Text or call your project manager directly. Their contact is given during orientation. If you can't reach them, call the main office at (813) 595-7663. We don't penalize for communication — we penalize for no-shows without a heads-up.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-q"><p class="font-medium text-brand-black text-sm">As a 1099, can I work for other roofing companies?</p><svg class="faq-arr" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#555" stroke-width="2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg></div>
        <div class="faq-a"><p style="color:#555555;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.7;padding-top:.5rem">Yes — you're an independent contractor, not an exclusive employee. However, while you're on an active Happy Roof job site or working a project for us, we expect your full attention and professional conduct. Non-compete clauses, if applicable, are outlined in your contractor agreement.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-q"><p class="font-medium text-brand-black text-sm">What if I see a safety issue on site?</p><svg class="faq-arr" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#555" stroke-width="2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg></div>
        <div class="faq-a"><p style="color:#555555;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.7;padding-top:.5rem">Stop work and report it to your crew lead or PM immediately. There's no penalty for flagging safety concerns — there's a serious consequence for ignoring them. We take OSHA compliance seriously and encourage every team member to speak up.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
        <div class="faq-q"><p class="font-medium text-brand-black text-sm">How can I move up within Happy Roof?</p><svg class="faq-arr" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#555" stroke-width="2"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg></div>
        <div class="faq-a"><p style="color:#555555;font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.7;padding-top:.5rem">We promote from within. Crew leads, field supervisors, and project managers have all come up from entry-level roles. Show up consistently, communicate well, and deliver quality work — those are the three things that get noticed. Bring it up in your 90-day review.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

